🎄🎄Christmas Is The Spirit Of Giving Without A Thought Of Getting🎄🎄
This is my favorite time of the year!!! One of my favorite times of the year is giving back to our delivery guys or women. It shows love and appreciation for all the hard work and overtime they do. I start with simple snacks and even make homemade special treats. On the last week, their busiest time, I place out Starbucks gift cards and make mini lunches. I receive a lot of packages a day, so I try to time them properly for the lunches. For the mailman, I tie a note that says for you mailman every few days. You may get a lot of your wrong-door neighbor packages on purpose doing this😚 I am truly my granny's grandbaby 🥹
If you want the label, DM me🤗

Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays from my family to yours❣️

I had so much fun on Christmas Eve!!! I remember growing up, and my granny and dad (Ace) would have all these gatherings. As a child, I prayed for a big enough home to always have a place to host anything for my family to have traditions and memories. I started hosting Maxiell Christmas Eve Pajama Party at my home every year in 2015 for my family. It’s a tradition I wanted to do for my family. I pray my son will continue and take over these same traditions when he gets older! #familyovereverything #thisiswhoidoitfor #familytradition #blackfamilylove
Maxiell's Take New York 🗽

I literally had the best time in New York!!! I decided last minute to take a trip because I wanted to get into the Christmas Holiday Spirit 🥰. I wish at 11 I could travel with a couple of my best friends and shop 5th Ave, sit right behind the bench at Madison Square Garden, go on the field to Met Life Stadium, and run around the city of New York like a rockstar!!! I thank God every day, all day, for blessing my family and me to be able to provide my son with these wonderfully memorable experiences that he will never forget...thank you, thank you, thank you!!!

Hey y'all, look what I done did 😝!! I got my booty done by the one and only @simonourianmd1 my friend, my guy!!! 
I lost about 40 lbs and a lot of volume in my butt...yes it's gone y'all 😆. But @simonourianmd1 help add some volume back by using filler. I didn't want to do a bbl, so he gave me this option. Over the next few weeks, I will see my butt plumper, more volume, and rounder. It was zero pain and zero downtime, which was a win-win for me...and it's FDA-approved!!!

LADIES AND FELLAS, if you don't like something about you, fix it. Who cares what other people think because I bet you the same ones judging had it done or wish they could. I met Dr. Simon at my most insecure times. Even though I was healed, blessed, and made it through cancer, it left some visible scars that took me a while to embrace. One was where my mediport was. It was so dark, ugly, and thick. I used to cover it up with my hair or alter my outfits to hide it until I met this doctor. He treated it and lasered it. Now I don't even notice it. At one point in time, I was breaking out so badly, and nothing worked on my face. He did this laser treatment on my face that cleared it immediately. People that followed me for a while all know my journey. 
I was one of Dr. Simon's first influencers and have referred so many people to him. I will always use him for any cosmetic procedure I decide to do because I trust him. Again love yourself first, then fix what needs to be done rather workout, surgery or whatever! It's 2023 live your best life!!! Love y'all 😘

Y'all I need your love and prayer for my baby @babyjasonmaxiell My sweet baby will be receiving Open Heart Surgery this week💔. I am severely crushed by the news we received weeks ago. As a parent, this has been the most challenging thing that I have gone through. I have yet to sleep or can wrap my head around this. I am so blessed that God could speak through to me to save my baby boy. We never knew our baby was at risk at any moment of a sudden cardiac arrest or unexpected death. When I think of that, that breaks me down. 
My baby has been strong through this all, and that is what has been getting us through. I haven't spoken about it because I needed to process this all and needed time with my family. But this is all in God’s hands, and I know he's covered and already healed. God knows all things and see all things and can do all things so that's why I put my trust in him. He will strengthen him with a new heart. He will watch over his own he already told me it's done he will go through a successful surgery. 
I would love for you all to pray for my baby as you prayed for us with covid. I felt the love the whole time in the hospital. I love you all and will keep you guys posted. Baby J is already committed once he's healed to get out and bring awareness to save others!! I love you all ❣️❤️ 
#pray #prayforbabyj #myPoohBear #yallPoohBear🥰

You got this Baby J🙏🏾💪🏾❤️ please pray for my baby 🫀❤️‍🩹❤️

#prayers #maxiellstrong #prayforbabyj #maxsquad
God Thank You For Everything 🙏🏾🫶🏾❤️

My baby is the strongest, toughest, and bravest kid I know❤️!! Waiting in the waiting room for 5 hours to see what was happening and then listening to the beeping machines to watchIng my baby in severe pain was so hard for me. @babyjasonmaxiell You’re strength, resilience, courage, fearlessness, and determination to go through this and to get through this have shown me a glimpse of your WHY and your PURPOSE...you are destined for greatness, and I can’t wait to watch❣️

I always have and will always worship you God. Thank you God for speaking through to me to save his life. Forever grateful and we are so blessed. Thank you God🙏🏾! 

Thank you all to those sent videos, who have called, texted, dm, came by, and sent flowers/gifts to lift his spirits and make sure he felt loved.  But most of all, thank you thank you thank you once again putting the Maxiell Family in your nightly prayers. We love you guys for that and will never forget it.

THIS was a Word and a MOMENT🔥 But last night that last part took me out. When she speaks, you listen. I am so proud to call the Potters House my church and home since 2000🙏🏾

Underneath it all I’ve been through some REAL LIFE TRAUMA that I’m still healing from. When I say my family have been tried and tested this year BELIEVE ME!!! A month ago I went through hernia surgery that left me in the hospital for 4 days. My bowel/intestines were strangulated by my hernia and deep in my belly button. That’s why my belly button will now look a little different. They went through my old scar that I had from when I had cancer. So I hope it will heal ok. But if it don’t I’m ok with that because I’m ALIVE. That thing could have gone septic and killed me at any moment if I wouldn’t have done the surgery soon enough. 
LADIES AND GENTS PLEASE DONT IGNORE YOUR BODY DO NOT DELAY ANYTHING MEDICALLY OR YOU WILL LEAVE BEHIND YOUR FAMILY SUFFERING. A hernia is nothing to delay or ignore!! I will do a more in depth IG LIVE or TIKTOK LIVE for the ones that have questions. 
But other than that I believe I am still here to bring awareness and help others. Pastor Sarah Jakes definitely did her thing at Women Evolve and I’m so happy I was able to attend and stand as long as I did. 
Thank you God for all that you have done for my family and I this year and I will forever repay you by honoring and worshiping you 🙏🏾

Reflecting on 2023: A Journey of Faith and Healing. This year, God redirected my path, challenging me with life-altering trials.  God gently steered me away from my plans, revealing His own design through life-altering surgeries between myself and my baby boy and unforeseen challenges.  It was a season of solitude, self-discovery, and family focus. A year where trauma met resilience.  It was a season of relying on God and knowing he was in control.  In the midst of trauma, I embraced the teachings of patience, prayer, and the art of survival, passing on these lessons to my dear ones—my Jasons. This wasn’t just a year; it was a period of reveal, battling the unknown, and ultimately, healing.  2024, I carry with me the restored strength of a mended family, ready for the promise of new beginnings. 2024 WILL be BIG! I CLAIM it and will receive everything that was lost plus gain EXTRA blessings that I didn’t even know I qualified for! God has a BIG BLESSING with MY name on it all 2024!

#HappyNewYear #2024 #breakthroughblessings #blessings
